    "intro": "Interpretation asks what the text means — moving from observation (what does it say?) to discerning the poet's intent in his canonical context. The movements below trace the psalm's argument from the priestly benediction through the double refrain to the eschatological harvest of fear. Where the Hebrew vocabulary sharpens what English translation flattens, a brief Greek/Hebrew note follows as supplement.",
